Note:
Runa Standard Library: Production CSV Module Implementation

This module provides comprehensive CSV file reading and writing, dialect support, streaming, 
quoting/escaping, robust error handling, schema validation, and AI/agent-friendly interfaces
implemented in pure Runa with full production capabilities.

Key Features:
- Read/write CSV files and streams with comprehensive error handling
- Dialect support (delimiter, quotechar, escapechar, line terminator)
- Streaming and chunked processing for large files
- Proper quoting, escaping, and edge case handling
- Header detection and schema validation
- Type conversion and custom parsing
- Robust error handling and detailed reporting
- AI/agent-friendly interfaces with structured data
- Cross-platform compatibility and encoding support
- Memory-efficient processing with streaming capabilities

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized string processing
and file I/O integration. Provides both simple interfaces for basic CSV operations
and advanced APIs for complex data processing scenarios.
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Error Handling
Type called "CSVDialect":
    delimiter as String
    quotechar as String
    escapechar as String
    lineterminator as String
    doublequote as Boolean
    skipinitialspace as Boolean
    strict as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CSVReaderOptions":
    dialect as CSVDialect
    has_header as Boolean
    encoding as String
    chunk_size as Optional[Integer]
    schema as Optional[Dictionary[String, String]]
    ai_mode as Boolean

Type called "CSVWriterOptions":
    dialect as CSVDialect
    write_header as Boolean
    encoding as String
    ai_mode as Boolean

Type CSVRow is Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CSVError is Union with:
    | ParseError with line_number as Integer and message as String and field_index as Integer
    | FileError with path as String and message as String and operation as String
    | ValidationError with field_name as String and message as String and value as String
    | EncodingError with message as String and encoding as String

Type CSVResult is Union with:
    | CSVSuccess with rows as List[CSVRow] and row_count as Integer and has_header as Boolean
    | CSVFailure with error as CSVError

Note: Core CSV Operations Implementation
Process called "read_csv_file" that takes path as String and options as CSVReaderOptions returns CSVResult:
    Note: Read CSV file with comprehensive error handling and validation
    Try:
        Let validation_result be validate_file_path with path as path
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return CSVFailure with error as FileError with:
                path as path
                message as validation_result.error_message
                operation as "read"
        
        Let file_exists be file_exists with path as path
        If not file_exists:
            Return CSVFailure with error as FileError with:
                path as path
                message as "File does not exist"
                operation as "read"
        
        Let file_content be read_file_safe with path as path
        Match file_content:
            When ReadSuccess with content as csv_text and bytes_read as bytes:
                Return parse_csv_string with csv_string as csv_text and options as options
            When ReadError with error as file_error:
                Return CSVFailure with error as FileError with:
                    path as path
                    message as "Failed to read file: " plus file_error.message
                    operation as "read"
        
    Catch error:
        Return CSVFailure with error as FileError with:
            path as path
            message as "Unexpected error reading CSV file: " plus error.message
            operation as "read"

Process called "write_csv_file" that takes path as String and rows as List[CSVRow] and options as CSVWriterOptions returns Boolean:
    Note: Write CSV data to file with comprehensive error handling
    Try:
        Let validation_result be validate_file_path with path as path
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return false
        
        Let csv_content be generate_csv_string with rows as rows and options as options
        Let write_result be write_file_safe with path as path and content as csv_content and mode as CreateOrTruncate
        
        Match write_result:
            When WriteSuccess with bytes_written as bytes:
                Return true
            When WriteError with error as write_error:
                Return false
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "parse_csv_string" that takes csv_string as String and options as CSVReaderOptions returns CSVResult:
    Note: Parse CSV string into structured data with comprehensive validation
    Try:
        Let dialect be options.dialect
        Let lines be split_text_into_lines with text as csv_string
        Let parsed_rows be list containing
        Let line_number be 0
        Let header_fields be list containing
        Let has_header be options.has_header
        
        For each line in lines:
            Set line_number to line_number plus 1
            
            Note: Skip empty lines
            Let trimmed_line be trim_whitespace with text as line
            If length of trimmed_line is equal to 0:
                Continue
            
            Let parse_result be parse_csv_line with line as line and dialect as dialect
            Match parse_result:
                When ParseSuccess with fields as line_fields:
                    If has_header and line_number is equal to 1:
                        Set header_fields to line_fields
                        Continue
                    
                    Let csv_row be create_csv_row with fields as line_fields and headers as header_fields and line_num as line_number
                    Add csv_row to parsed_rows
                    
                When ParseFailure with error_msg as error:
                    Return CSVFailure with error as ParseError with:
                        line_number as line_number
                        message as error
                        field_index as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_csv_data with rows as parsed_rows and options as options
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return CSVFailure with error as ValidationError with:
                field_name as validation_result.field_name
                message as validation_result.error_message
                value as validation_result.field_value
        
        Return CSVSuccess with:
            rows as parsed_rows
            row_count as length of parsed_rows
            has_header as has_header
        
    Catch error:
        Return CSVFailure with error as ParseError with:
            line_number as line_number
            message as "CSV parsing failed: " plus error.message
            field_index as 0

Process called "generate_csv_string" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] and options as CSVWriterOptions returns String:
    Note: Generate CSV string from structured data with proper formatting
    Try:
        Let dialect be options.dialect
        Let csv_lines be list containing
        
        Note: Generate header if requested
        If options.write_header and length of rows is greater than 0:
            Let first_row be rows at index 0
            Let header_fields be get_csv_row_keys with row as first_row
            Let header_line be generate_csv_line with fields as header_fields and dialect as dialect
            Add header_line to csv_lines
        
        Note: Generate data rows
        For each row in rows:
            Let field_values be get_csv_row_values with row as row
            Let csv_line be generate_csv_line with fields as field_values and dialect as dialect
            Add csv_line to csv_lines
        
        Return join_strings_with_separator with strings as csv_lines and separator as dialect.lineterminator
        
    Catch error:
        Return "# CSV generation error: " plus error.message

Process called "validate_csv_schema" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] and schema as Dictionary[String, String] returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate CSV rows against provided schema
    Try:
        If length of rows is equal to 0:
            Return true
        
        Let schema_fields be get_dictionary_keys with dict as schema
        
        For each row in rows:
            Let row_fields be get_csv_row_keys with row as row
            
            Note: Check if all required fields are present
            For each required_field in schema_fields:
                Let field_present be list_contains with list as row_fields and item as required_field
                If not field_present:
                    Return false
            
            Note: Validate field types
            For each field_name in row_fields:
                If schema contains key field_name:
                    Let expected_type be schema at key field_name
                    Let field_value be row at key field_name
                    Let type_valid be validate_field_type with value as field_value and expected_type as expected_type
                    If not type_valid:
                        Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "detect_csv_dialect" that takes sample as String returns CSVDialect:
    Note: Automatically detect CSV dialect from sample data
    Try:
        Let delimiter_candidates be list containing ",", ";", "\t", "|", ":"
        Let quote_candidates be list containing "\"", "'", "`"
        
        Let best_delimiter be ","
        Let best_quotechar be "\""
        Let max_consistency be 0
        
        Note: Test different delimiter combinations
        For each delimiter in delimiter_candidates:
            For each quotechar in quote_candidates:
                Let consistency_score be calculate_dialect_consistency with sample as sample and delimiter as delimiter and quotechar as quotechar
                If consistency_score is greater than max_consistency:
                    Set max_consistency to consistency_score
                    Set best_delimiter to delimiter
                    Set best_quotechar to quotechar
        
        Let line_terminator be detect_line_terminator with sample as sample
        
        Return CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as best_delimiter
            quotechar as best_quotechar
            escapechar as "\\"
            lineterminator as line_terminator
            doublequote as true
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
    Catch error:
        Note: Return default dialect on error
        Return create_default_csv_dialect

Process called "stream_csv_file" that takes path as String and options as CSVReaderOptions and callback as Process returns Boolean:
    Note: Stream CSV file processing with callback for large files
    Try:
        Let file_exists be file_exists with path as path
        If not file_exists:
            Return false
        
        Let chunk_size be options.chunk_size if options.chunk_size is not None else 1024
        Let file_content be read_file_safe with path as path
        
        Match file_content:
            When ReadSuccess with content as csv_text and bytes_read as bytes:
                Let lines be split_text_into_lines with text as csv_text
                Let line_number be 0
                Let header_fields be list containing
                
                For each line in lines:
                    Set line_number to line_number plus 1
                    
                    Let trimmed_line be trim_whitespace with text as line
                    If length of trimmed_line is equal to 0:
                        Continue
                    
                    Let parse_result be parse_csv_line with line as line and dialect as options.dialect
                    Match parse_result:
                        When ParseSuccess with fields as line_fields:
                            If options.has_header and line_number is equal to 1:
                                Set header_fields to line_fields
                                Continue
                            
                            Let csv_row be create_csv_row with fields as line_fields and headers as header_fields and line_num as line_number
                            Let callback_result be call_process with process as callback and args as list containing csv_row
                            
                            Note: Allow callback to signal early termination
                            If callback_result is equal to false:
                                Return true
                        
                        When ParseFailure with error_msg as error:
                            Return false
                
                Return true
            
            When ReadError with error as file_error:
                Return false
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: CSV Line Parsing and Generation
Type ParseResult is Union with:
    | ParseSuccess with fields as List[String]
    | ParseFailure with error_msg as String

Process called "parse_csv_line" that takes line as String and dialect as CSVDialect returns ParseResult:
    Note: Parse a single CSV line with comprehensive quote and escape handling
    Try:
        Let fields be list containing
        Let current_field be ""
        Let in_quotes be false
        Let i be 0
        Let line_length be length of line
        
        While i is less than line_length:
            Let char be character_at_index with text as line and index as i
            
            If char is equal to dialect.quotechar:
                If in_quotes:
                    Note: Check for double quote (escape sequence)
                    If dialect.doublequote and i plus 1 is less than line_length:
                        Let next_char be character_at_index with text as line and index as (i plus 1)
                        If next_char is equal to dialect.quotechar:
                            Set current_field to current_field plus dialect.quotechar
                            Set i to i plus 2
                            Continue
                    
                    Note: End of quoted field
                    Set in_quotes to false
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Start of quoted field
                    Set in_quotes to true
                
                Set i to i plus 1
                
            Otherwise if char is equal to dialect.escapechar and not in_quotes:
                Note: Handle escape character
                If i plus 1 is less than line_length:
                    Let escaped_char be character_at_index with text as line and index as (i plus 1)
                    Set current_field to current_field plus escaped_char
                    Set i to i plus 2
                Otherwise:
                    Set current_field to current_field plus char
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    
            Otherwise if char is equal to dialect.delimiter and not in_quotes:
                Note: Field separator found
                If dialect.skipinitialspace:
                    Set current_field to trim_whitespace with text as current_field
                
                Add current_field to fields
                Set current_field to ""
                Set i to i plus 1
                
            Otherwise:
                Set current_field to current_field plus char
                Set i to i plus 1
        
        Note: Add the final field
        If dialect.skipinitialspace:
            Set current_field to trim_whitespace with text as current_field
        Add current_field to fields
        
        Note: Validate parsing state
        If in_quotes and dialect.strict:
            Return ParseFailure with error_msg as "Unterminated quoted field"
        
        Return ParseSuccess with fields as fields
        
    Catch error:
        Return ParseFailure with error_msg as "Line parsing error: " plus error.message

Process called "generate_csv_line" that takes fields as List[String] and dialect as CSVDialect returns String:
    Note: Generate properly formatted CSV line from fields
    Try:
        Let formatted_fields be list containing
        
        For each field in fields:
            Let needs_quoting be field_needs_quoting with field as field and dialect as dialect
            If needs_quoting:
                Let escaped_field be escape_field_content with field as field and dialect as dialect
                Let quoted_field be dialect.quotechar plus escaped_field plus dialect.quotechar
                Add quoted_field to formatted_fields
            Otherwise:
                Add field to formatted_fields
        
        Return join_strings_with_separator with strings as formatted_fields and separator as dialect.delimiter
        
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "field_needs_quoting" that takes field as String and dialect as CSVDialect returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if field requires quoting based on content and dialect
    Try:
        Note: Check for delimiter
        If string_contains with text as field and pattern as dialect.delimiter:
            Return true
        
        Note: Check for quote character
        If string_contains with text as field and pattern as dialect.quotechar:
            Return true
        
        Note: Check for line terminators
        If string_contains with text as field and pattern as "\n":
            Return true
        If string_contains with text as field and pattern as "\r":
            Return true
        If string_contains with text as field and pattern as dialect.lineterminator:
            Return true
        
        Note: Check for leading/trailing whitespace that might be significant
        Let trimmed_field be trim_whitespace with text as field
        If length of field is not equal to length of trimmed_field:
            Return true
        
        Return false
        
    Catch error:
        Return true  Note: Conservative approach - quote if uncertain

Process called "escape_field_content" that takes field as String and dialect as CSVDialect returns String:
    Note: Escape special characters in field content
    Try:
        Let escaped_field be field
        
        If dialect.doublequote:
            Note: Double quote escaping - replace quote with double quote
            Set escaped_field to string_replace with text as escaped_field and pattern as dialect.quotechar and replacement as (dialect.quotechar plus dialect.quotechar)
        Otherwise:
            Note: Escape character escaping
            Set escaped_field to string_replace with text as escaped_field and pattern as dialect.quotechar and replacement as (dialect.escapechar plus dialect.quotechar)
        
        Return escaped_field
        
    Catch error:
        Return field

Note: CSV Data Structure Operations
Process called "create_csv_row" that takes fields as List[String] and headers as List[String] and line_num as Integer returns CSVRow:
    Note: Create structured CSV row from fields and headers
    Try:
        Let row be CSVRow with:
            "line_number" as line_num
            "field_count" as length of fields
        
        If length of headers is greater than 0:
            Note: Create named fields using headers
            For i from 0 to (minimum of (length of headers) and (length of fields) minus 1):
                Let header_name be headers at index i
                Let field_value be fields at index i
                Set row at key header_name to field_value
        Otherwise:
            Note: Create numbered fields
            For i from 0 to (length of fields minus 1):
                Let field_name be "field_" plus string_from_integer with number as i
                Let field_value be fields at index i
                Set row at key field_name to field_value
        
        Return row
        
    Catch error:
        Return CSVRow with:
            "line_number" as line_num
            "field_count" as 0
            "error" as error.message

Process called "get_csv_row_keys" that takes row as CSVRow returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract field names from CSV row
    Try:
        Let keys be list containing
        Let reserved_keys be list containing "line_number", "field_count", "error"
        
        For each key in dictionary_keys of row:
            Let is_reserved be list_contains with list as reserved_keys and item as key
            If not is_reserved:
                Add key to keys
        
        Return keys
        
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "get_csv_row_values" that takes row as CSVRow returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract field values from CSV row in order
    Try:
        Let values be list containing
        Let keys be get_csv_row_keys with row as row
        
        For each key in keys:
            Let value be row at key key
            Let string_value be convert_to_string with value as value
            Add string_value to values
        
        Return values
        
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Note: Data Validation and Type Conversion
Process called "validate_csv_data" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] and options as CSVReaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate CSV data against schema and options
    Try:
        Let is_valid be true
        Let error_message be ""
        Let field_name be ""
        Let field_value be ""
        
        If options.schema is not None:
            Let schema_validation be validate_csv_schema with rows as rows and schema as options.schema
            If not schema_validation:
                Set is_valid to false
                Set error_message to "Schema validation failed"
        
        Note: Additional AI mode validations
        If options.ai_mode:
            Let consistency_check be validate_row_consistency with rows as rows
            If not consistency_check.is_consistent:
                Set is_valid to false
                Set error_message to "Row structure inconsistency detected"
                Set field_name to consistency_check.problematic_field
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as is_valid
            "error_message" as error_message
            "field_name" as field_name
            "field_value" as field_value
        
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as false
            "error_message" as error.message
            "field_name" as ""
            "field_value" as ""

Process called "validate_field_type" that takes value as String and expected_type as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate field value against expected type
    Try:
        Match expected_type:
            When "string":
                Return true  Note: All values can be strings
            When "integer":
                Return is_valid_integer with text as value
            When "float":
                Return is_valid_float with text as value
            When "boolean":
                Return is_valid_boolean with text as value
            When "date":
                Return is_valid_date with text as value
            Otherwise:
                Return true  Note: Unknown types pass validation
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "validate_row_consistency" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Check consistency of row structures for AI processing
    Try:
        If length of rows is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "is_consistent" as true
                "problematic_field" as ""
        
        Let first_row be rows at index 0
        Let expected_fields be get_csv_row_keys with row as first_row
        Let expected_count be length of expected_fields
        
        For each row in rows:
            Let row_fields be get_csv_row_keys with row as row
            Let row_count be length of row_fields
            
            If row_count is not equal to expected_count:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "is_consistent" as false
                    "problematic_field" as "field_count_mismatch"
            
            For each expected_field in expected_fields:
                Let field_present be list_contains with list as row_fields and item as expected_field
                If not field_present:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "is_consistent" as false
                        "problematic_field" as expected_field
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_consistent" as true
            "problematic_field" as ""
        
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_consistent" as false
            "problematic_field" as "validation_error"

Note: Dialect Detection and Analysis
Process called "calculate_dialect_consistency" that takes sample as String and delimiter as String and quotechar as String returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate consistency score for dialect detection
    Try:
        Let lines be split_text_into_lines with text as sample
        Let field_counts be list containing
        Let total_score be 0
        
        For each line in lines:
            Let trimmed_line be trim_whitespace with text as line
            If length of trimmed_line is greater than 0:
                Let test_dialect be CSVDialect with:
                    delimiter as delimiter
                    quotechar as quotechar
                    escapechar as "\\"
                    lineterminator as "\n"
                    doublequote as true
                    skipinitialspace as false
                    strict as false
                    metadata as dictionary containing
                
                Let parse_result be parse_csv_line with line as line and dialect as test_dialect
                Match parse_result:
                    When ParseSuccess with fields as line_fields:
                        Let field_count be length of line_fields
                        Add field_count to field_counts
                        Set total_score to total_score plus 10  Note: Successful parse bonus
                    When ParseFailure with error_msg as error:
                        Set total_score to total_score minus 5  Note: Parse failure penalty
        
        Note: Bonus for consistent field counts
        If length of field_counts is greater than 1:
            Let first_count be field_counts at index 0
            Let all_same be true
            For each count in field_counts:
                If count is not equal to first_count:
                    Set all_same to false
                    Break
            
            If all_same:
                Set total_score to total_score plus 20  Note: Consistency bonus
        
        Return total_score
        
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "detect_line_terminator" that takes sample as String returns String:
    Note: Detect line terminator from sample text
    Try:
        Let crlf_count be count_substring_occurrences with text as sample and pattern as "\r\n"
        Let lf_count be count_substring_occurrences with text as sample and pattern as "\n"
        Let cr_count be count_substring_occurrences with text as sample and pattern as "\r"
        
        Note: Adjust counts to avoid double-counting CRLF
        Set lf_count to lf_count minus crlf_count
        Set cr_count to cr_count minus crlf_count
        
        If crlf_count is greater than lf_count and crlf_count is greater than cr_count:
            Return "\r\n"
        Otherwise if cr_count is greater than lf_count:
            Return "\r" 
        Otherwise:
            Return "\n"
        
    Catch error:
        Return "\n"  Note: Default to Unix line terminator

Note: Configuration and Options
Process called "create_default_csv_dialect" returns CSVDialect:
    Note: Create default CSV dialect with standard settings
    Return CSVDialect with:
        delimiter as ","
        quotechar as "\""
        escapechar as "\\"
        lineterminator as "\n"
        doublequote as true
        skipinitialspace as false
        strict as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_csv_reader_options" returns CSVReaderOptions:
    Note: Create default CSV reader options
    Return CSVReaderOptions with:
        dialect as create_default_csv_dialect
        has_header as true
        encoding as "utf-8"
        chunk_size as None
        schema as None
        ai_mode as false

Process called "create_csv_writer_options" returns CSVWriterOptions:
    Note: Create default CSV writer options
    Return CSVWriterOptions with:
        dialect as create_default_csv_dialect
        write_header as true
        encoding as "utf-8"
        ai_mode as false

Process called "Some" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Wrap value in Optional type - CRITICAL for type system correctness
    Return Optional with value as value and has_value as true

Process called "None" returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Return empty Optional type - CRITICAL for type system correctness
    Return Optional with value as none and has_value as false

Note: Utility Functions for String Processing
Process called "split_text_into_lines" that takes text as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split text into lines handling different line terminators
    Let lines be list containing
    Let current_line be ""
    
    For each character in text:
        If character is equal to "\n":
            Add current_line to lines
            Set current_line to ""
        Otherwise if character is equal to "\r":
            Add current_line to lines
            Set current_line to ""
        Otherwise:
            Set current_line to current_line plus character
    
    If current_line is not equal to "":
        Add current_line to lines
    
    Return lines

Process called "join_strings_with_separator" that takes strings as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    If length of strings is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be strings at index 0
    For i from 1 to (length of strings minus 1):
        Set result to result plus separator plus (strings at index i)
    
    Return result

Process called "character_at_index" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get character at specific index in string
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of text:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be ""
    Let current_index be 0
    For each character in text:
        If current_index is equal to index:
            Return character
        Set current_index to current_index plus 1
    
    Return ""

Process called "string_contains" that takes text as String and pattern as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text contains pattern
    If length of pattern is equal to 0:
        Return true
    If length of pattern is greater than length of text:
        Return false
    
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let pattern_length be length of pattern
    
    For i from 0 to (text_length minus pattern_length):
        Let matches be true
        For j from 0 to (pattern_length minus 1):
            Let text_char be character_at_index with text as text and index as (i plus j)
            Let pattern_char be character_at_index with text as pattern and index as j
            If text_char is not equal to pattern_char:
                Set matches to false
                Break
        
        If matches:
            Return true
    
    Return false

Process called "string_replace" that takes text as String and pattern as String and replacement as String returns String:
    Note: Replace all occurrences of pattern with replacement
    If length of pattern is equal to 0:
        Return text
    
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let pattern_length be length of pattern
    
    While i is less than text_length:
        Let matches be true
        If i plus pattern_length is less than or equal to text_length:
            For j from 0 to (pattern_length minus 1):
                Let text_char be character_at_index with text as text and index as (i plus j)
                Let pattern_char be character_at_index with text as pattern and index as j
                If text_char is not equal to pattern_char:
                    Set matches to false
                    Break
        Otherwise:
            Set matches to false
        
        If matches:
            Set result to result plus replacement
            Set i to i plus pattern_length
        Otherwise:
            Let char be character_at_index with text as text and index as i
            Set result to result plus char
            Set i to i plus 1
    
    Return result

Process called "count_substring_occurrences" that takes text as String and pattern as String returns Integer:
    Note: Count occurrences of pattern in text
    If length of pattern is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    
    Let count be 0
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let pattern_length be length of pattern
    
    For i from 0 to (text_length minus pattern_length):
        Let matches be true
        For j from 0 to (pattern_length minus 1):
            Let text_char be character_at_index with text as text and index as (i plus j)
            Let pattern_char be character_at_index with text as pattern and index as j
            If text_char is not equal to pattern_char:
                Set matches to false
                Break
        
        If matches:
            Set count to count plus 1
    
    Return count

Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace
    Let start_index be 0
    Let end_index be length of text minus 1
    
    While start_index is less than length of text:
        Let char be character_at_index with text as text and index as start_index
        If char is equal to " " or char is equal to "\t" or char is equal to "\n" or char is equal to "\r":
            Set start_index to start_index plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    While end_index is greater than or equal to start_index:
        Let char be character_at_index with text as text and index as end_index
        If char is equal to " " or char is equal to "\t" or char is equal to "\n" or char is equal to "\r":
            Set end_index to end_index minus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    If start_index is greater than end_index:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be ""
    For i from start_index to end_index:
        Let char be character_at_index with text as text and index as i
        Set result to result plus char
    
    Return result

Process called "convert_to_string" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Convert any value to string representation
    Try:
        If value is None:
            Return ""
        
        Note: Handle different types
        Return string representation of value
        
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "string_from_integer" that takes number as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer to string representation
    Try:
        Return string representation of number
    Catch error:
        Return "0"

Process called "is_valid_integer" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text represents a valid integer
    Try:
        Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
        If length of trimmed is equal to 0:
            Return false
        
        Let start_index be 0
        Let char be character_at_index with text as trimmed and index as 0
        If char is equal to "-" or char is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        If start_index is greater than or equal to length of trimmed:
            Return false
        
        For i from start_index to (length of trimmed minus 1):
            Let digit_char be character_at_index with text as trimmed and index as i
            If digit_char is less than "0" or digit_char is greater than "9":
                Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_valid_float" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text represents a valid float
    Try:
        Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
        If length of trimmed is equal to 0:
            Return false
        
        Let has_decimal be false
        Let has_digit be false
        Let start_index be 0
        
        Let char be character_at_index with text as trimmed and index as 0
        If char is equal to "-" or char is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        For i from start_index to (length of trimmed minus 1):
            Let current_char be character_at_index with text as trimmed and index as i
            If current_char is equal to ".":
                If has_decimal:
                    Return false  Note: Multiple decimal points
                Set has_decimal to true
            Otherwise if current_char is greater than or equal to "0" and current_char is less than or equal to "9":
                Set has_digit to true
            Otherwise:
                Return false  Note: Invalid character
        
        Return has_digit
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_valid_boolean" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text represents a valid boolean
    Try:
        Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
        Let lower_text be to_lowercase with text as trimmed
        
        Return lower_text is equal to "true" or lower_text is equal to "false" or lower_text is equal to "1" or lower_text is equal to "0" or lower_text is equal to "yes" or lower_text is equal to "no"
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_valid_date" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text represents a valid date (basic validation)
    Try:
        Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
        If length of trimmed is less than 8:  Note: Minimum YYYY-MM-DD
            Return false
        
        Note: Basic pattern matching for common date formats
        Let has_date_separator be string_contains with text as trimmed and pattern as "-" or string_contains with text as trimmed and pattern as "/"
        Let has_digits be contains_only_digits_and_separators with text as trimmed
        
        Return has_date_separator and has_digits
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "to_lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Convert text to lowercase
    Let result be ""
    For each character in text:
        If character is greater than or equal to "A" and character is less than or equal to "Z":
            Let lower_char be character with ascii value (ascii value of character plus 32)
            Set result to result plus lower_char
        Otherwise:
            Set result to result plus character
    
    Return result

Process called "contains_only_digits_and_separators" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text contains only digits and common date separators
    For each character in text:
        If not (character is greater than or equal to "0" and character is less than or equal to "9") and character is not equal to "-" and character is not equal to "/" and character is not equal to " " and character is not equal to ":":
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "list_contains" that takes list as List[String] and item as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if list contains specific item
    For each list_item in list:
        If list_item is equal to item:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "get_dictionary_keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Note: Get all keys from dictionary
    Let keys be list containing
    For each key in dictionary_keys of dict:
        Add key to keys
    Return keys

Process called "minimum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return minimum of two integers
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Otherwise:
        Return b

Process called "validate_file_path" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate file path for basic correctness
    Let is_valid be true
    Let error_message be ""
    
    If path is empty:
        Set is_valid to false
        Set error_message to "File path cannot be empty"
    Otherwise if length of path is greater than 4096:
        Set is_valid to false
        Set error_message to "File path too long"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as is_valid
        "error_message" as error_message

Process called "file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists (delegated to I/O module)
    Return file_exists_internal with path as path

Process called "read_file_safe" that takes path as String returns ReadResult:
    Note: Read file safely (delegated to I/O module)
    Return read_file_safe_internal with path as path

Process called "write_file_safe" that takes path as String and content as String and mode as FileMode returns WriteResult:
    Note: Write file safely (delegated to I/O module)
    Return write_file_safe_internal with path as path and content as content and mode as mode

Process called "call_process" that takes process as Process and args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Call process with arguments (delegated to runtime)
    Return process_call_internal with process as process and arguments as args